                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17814" author="gmazza" created="Thu, 1 Jun 2006 06:37:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I recall correctly, one of the problems with Struts is that much of its tag libraries overlapped with what is already available with JSTL, as well as the team in general having problems getting enough volunteers to maintain their tag libraries.  Is Spring repeating this mistake--would these changes be duplicating JSTL&apos;s functionality?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Glen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17819" author="condor" created="Thu, 1 Jun 2006 18:53:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree that some of this functionality (properties for title, alt, accesskey and label) can be duplicated by using the spring + html taglib, e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;spring:message code=&quot;messageCode&quot; var=&quot;labelVar&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;form:item value=&quot;someValue&quot; label=&quot;$&lt;/p&gt;
{labelVar}
&lt;p&gt;&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;instead of&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;form:item value=&quot;someValue&quot; labelCode=&quot;messageCode&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The only property that can&apos;t be handled this way is the itemLabel property of the items tag.&lt;br/&gt;
Currently, I need to use code in the controller to prepare the value for the items property, so it contains the resolved message.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17828" author="gmazza" created="Thu, 1 Jun 2006 22:02:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the explanation.  I think I understand now (I have not looked at the 2.0 Spring tags yet), and like your simplification.  If the &amp;lt;form:item/&amp;gt; tag already exists, then better filling out its functionality would seem to make sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Glen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23646" author="pmularien" created="Thu, 10 May 2007 08:35:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sounds an awful lot like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2566&quot; title=&quot;&amp;lt;form:label/&amp;gt; should have MessageSource support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2566&quot;&gt;SPR-2566&lt;/a&gt;, also assigned to 2.1RC1. Any chance the bugs could be consolidated?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
